description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;‘Making a difference for you, with you’&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have 1 fixed term maternity leave vacancy for a Speech and Language Therapist to work with preschool and school aged children in Northamptonshire. The fixed term contract will be for 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts involve:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing speech and language therapy support and intervention to children attending community clinics, pre-school settings, mainstream and special schools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate a clear motivation/ enthusiasm for working with children and families and a commitment to the provision of training and collaborative working with other professionals in the wider multi-agency team. We can offer support through regular team meetings, group and individual supervision sessions and continuous professional development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Maggie Allen&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title SALT Team Facilitator for Community &amp; Mainstream&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Maggie.allen@nhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07860784267&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maggie. Allen, SLT facilitator for Community &amp; Mainstream on 07860784267 or by email: Maggie.allen@nhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Foster, SLT facilitator for Community &amp; Mainstream on 07789924566 or by email: susan.foster@nhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
